OL,4,C'must be all or nothing', campaigners
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FInquest has published a report after
OL,8,Fbringing together "powerful voices of
OL,9,Fbereaved families, victims and
OL,10,Fsurvivors of some of the worst
OL,11,Ffailings of public services and the
OL,12,Flegal system in the UK" to re-state
OL,13,Fthe need for a strong law.
OL,15,FIn it, Inquest director, Deborah Coles
OL,16,Fsaid the law "must be 'all or
OL,17,Fnothing', without dilution or caveat,
OL,18,Fto ensure the response to contentious
OL,19,Fdeaths, harms and grave injustices
OL,20,Fdramatically improves".
